# The Legal and Political Effects of the Dred Scott Decision

## Executive Summary

The Dred Scott decision, delivered by the U.S. Supreme Court in 1857, is one of the most infamous rulings in American history. It had profound legal and political ramifications, exacerbating sectional tensions and contributing to the onset of the American Civil War. The decision declared that African Americans could not be U.S. citizens and that Congress had no authority to prohibit slavery in U.S. territories. This ruling invalidated previous compromises and heightened national divisions over slavery.

